  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Prose reads smooth when it is typed smooth - no stumbles, no breaks. Loop each word until it glides, then carry that ease into the full passage. Flow, not force."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Hands on home row, eyes off the keys. Repeat each word at one even pace - same gap between every tap. Don't push the pace, let the steady beat hold it for you."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "🎶",
      "title": "Even beat",
      "text": "Set a tempo you can hold the whole way through. Smooth and even beats fast and jerky every time - flowing prose comes from a flowing hand. Trust the rhythm and let it carry you."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "walked",
      "baseReps": 5,
      "keys": ["w", "a", "l", "k", "e", "d"],
      "target": "walked walked walked walked walked",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "Rhythm: walked",
      "hint": "Loop it on the beat: walked - walked - walked. Same gap every time."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "silence",
      "baseReps": 4,
      "keys": ["s", "i", "l", "e", "n", "c"],
      "target": "silence silence silence silence",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "Rhythm: silence",
      "hint": "Hold the tempo: silence - silence - silence. Flow, not force."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "garden",
      "baseReps": 4,
      "keys": ["g", "a", "r", "d", "e", "n"],
      "target": "garden garden garden garden",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Rhythm: garden",
      "hint": "Stay even to the end: garden - garden - garden. Don't rush the finish."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Feel the longer words flowing as one smooth move instead of a chain of letters? That is what makes prose glide - even reps turn effort into reflex, and reflex keeps the sentence unbroken."
    },
    {
